---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import InfoBox from '../components/InfoBox.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About The Breed | Monarch Chihuahuas"
  description="Learn about the Chihuahua breed - history, characteristics, and what makes them such devoted little companions."
  keywords="chihuahua, teacup chihuahua, apple head chihuahua, chihuahua breed, chihuahua facts"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="About The Breed"
    subtitle="Discover what makes Chihuahuas such beloved companions"
  />

  <section class="info-content">
    <div class="content-container">
      <h2>The Chihuahua: A Beloved Family Companion</h2>
      <p>The Chihuahua is the smallest recognized dog breed in the world — but don't let the size fool you. These tiny, expressive dogs are bold, loyal, and bursting with personality. Originally from Mexico and named after the Mexican state of Chihuahua, they have been treasured pocket-sized companions for centuries.</p>

      <h3>The Chihuahua Family</h3>
      <p>At Monarch Chihuahuas, we raise the most beloved varieties of this charming breed:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Smooth-Coat Chihuahuas:</strong> Sleek, low-maintenance coats that come in nearly every color imaginable.</li>
        <li><strong>Long-Coat Chihuahuas:</strong> Soft, flowing fur with feathered ears and tail — still small, but with a glamorous look.</li>
        <li><strong>Apple-Head Chihuahuas:</strong> The classic AKC standard — rounded head, large expressive eyes, and the signature confident stance.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Physical Characteristics</h3>
      <p>Chihuahuas are tiny but sturdy, with a confident posture and the most expressive faces in the dog world.</p>

      <InfoBox type="info" title="Size">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Weight:</strong> 2–6 lbs (AKC standard caps at 6 lbs)</li>
          <li><strong>Height:</strong> 5–8 inches at the shoulder</li>
          <li><strong>Build:</strong> Compact, balanced, and surprisingly muscular for their size</li>
        </ul>
      </InfoBox>

      <InfoBox type="info" title="Coat">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Type:</strong> Smooth (short) or long-coat varieties</li>
          <li><strong>Maintenance:</strong> Weekly brushing for smooth coats, 2–3x weekly for long coats</li>
          <li><strong>Shedding:</strong> Moderate — manageable with regular brushing</li>
        </ul>
      </InfoBox>

      <h3>Colors and Patterns</h3>
      <p>Our chihuahuas come in a beautiful range of colors:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Solids:</strong> Fawn, cream, chocolate, black, white, blue, and red</li>
        <li><strong>Marked:</strong> Sable, brindle, and merle patterns</li>
        <li><strong>Parti:</strong> Striking two- and three-tone combinations</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Temperament</h3>
      <p>Chihuahuas are known for their:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Devotion:</strong> Famously bond closely with one or two special people</li>
        <li><strong>Intelligence:</strong> Quick learners with sharp minds</li>
        <li><strong>Confidence:</strong> Big personality in a tiny body — fearless and bold</li>
        <li><strong>Affection:</strong> Love to be carried, cuddled, and kept close</li>
        <li><strong>Adaptability:</strong> Perfect for apartments, RVs, or homes of any size</li>
        <li><strong>Alertness:</strong> Naturally watchful — they make excellent little watchdogs</li>
      </ul>

      <InfoBox type="paw" title="Did You Know?">
        <p>Chihuahuas have the longest lifespan of any dog breed — many live 14 to 20 years with proper care. They are also one of the oldest recognized breeds in the Americas, with ancestors traced back to the ancient Techichi dogs of pre-Columbian Mexico.</p>
      </InfoBox>

      <h3>Life Expectancy</h3>
      <p>With proper care, chihuahuas typically live 14–18 years, making them one of the longest-lived companions you can welcome into your home.</p>

      <div class="cta-box">
        <h3>Ready to Welcome a Chihuahua?</h3>
        <p>Browse our available puppies and find your perfect tiny match.</p>
        <a href="/available-puppies" class="btn">View Available Puppies</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .info-content {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .content-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #2B2018;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: #5a5a5a;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    color: #5a5a5a;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta-box {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary), var(--color-primary));
    color: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .cta-box h3 {
    color: white;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .cta-box p {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    padding: 0.875rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: var(--color-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .info-content {
      padding: 3rem 1rem;
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }

    h3 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
